tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows mildly elevated creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glycosuria, ketonuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance, indicating possible renal dysfunction and/or poorly controlled diabetes, despite low HbA1c (which may be unreliable in elderly or anemic patients). No evidence of urinary infection. Recommend further evaluation of renal function, diabetes status, and possible causes for abnormal urine findings.
